node.text:
2 Keys to Dealing with Imposter Syndrome -

first of all, let’s define it 

imposter syndrome is where you feel like you aren’t good enough, prepared enough ,knowledgeable enough, or worthy of your current position in life …

like if people knew the real you maybe you wouldn’t be where you are …

Here’s the Truth: I’ve dealt with this most of my professional career … 

but here’s the key- imposter syndrome is both REAL and GOOD if you use it wisely 

Here’s 2 Keys to winning inspite of  imposter syndrome :

1. Remember You bring value: No matter where you are you have value to bring to people. You might not be at the goal but you are further along your path than those coming behind you and they will find great value in the lessons you’ve learned ahead of them.

2. Imposter Syndrome Is your subconscious telling you to improve. You feel uncomfortable because you KNOW you could be better than you are. Use that feeling to push you towards developing your skills and abilities at a greater level 

never ever forget this truth : DONT LET WHAT YOU THINK YOU AREN’T STOP YOU FROM EVERYTHING YOU ARE

So Jess and I have some  bittersweet news to share with you all. 

It’s been a little while in the making but we are officially moving FULL TIME to Florida next month🏖🏖🏖 and we will be transitioning this incredible Ranch Estate Into our Vacation Rental Portfolio Of Properties! 

As many of you know we have been permanent florida residents for the last 3 years but would come back to michigan for the summertimes.

When we purchased the ranch and started building this incredible home we had no intention of ever permanently living in florida 

and while we will always be back in Michigan to see friends and family, 5 years later, we can’t help but call Florida our home. 🏡 

We will be transitioning this property into our vacation rental portfolio starting in mid August! Its simply too great of a property not to share with the world !

This property is simply unmatched when it comes to the perfect spot for family lake getaways , corporate retreats, weddings, family reunions or just some incredible time in the great outdoors. Just one hour from DTW and 15 minutes from FNT airports it sleeps 24 and is an place to unplug and refocus on what’s most important. 

This 8 bed 7.5 bath 13,000sq ft estate property is situated on 8.5 acres with over 1000 feet of public all sports lake frontage, a 200 ft private beach, 3 slip boat dock, paddle boards kayaks and incredible memories.  Check out the pics above and the link in my bio for availability and pricing and we hope you enjoy this property as much as we have

node.text:
I’ve never been the best at anything

it almost everything that I’ve ever done there have been people who have been far more talented than I 

but life and success are a marathon not a sprint and hard work beats talent when talent isn’t working hard

no matter where you’re starting from or how far behind you think you might be, remember that somebody else’s game has virtually no effect on how you play your game. 

 I would like to share with you three things that helped me play my game

1. Learning myself- I think the first step to really succeeding is being very clear on who you are, what you want and why you want it.  you also need to know HOW you are : in other words, what are the things that tend to distract or immobilize you and how do you eliminate those from your life? how are you motivated and how do you leverage those things to keep going long after other people stop

2. self improving daily- we can’t go into a bright new future our same old junky self. The fact is we’ve gotten as far as we’re ever going to get with the mindset and skill set we currently have. if we want to upgrade our results we’ve got a upgrade our  thinking belief systems and actions.

3. be relentless- how bad do you want it? No, really, how bad do you want it? What’s it gonna take to get you to quit? what’s it going to take to get you to break?  if you wanna win big in life you’re gonna have to go way past those things. most of success is about holding on after everybody else let’s go. it’s about believing one more time, dreaming one more time, going for it one more time; and then doing it again tomorrow and the day after that and the day after that for years. 

so what’s the point of this? 

You don’t have to be the best to win in a big way or to live an incredible life and make a big difference. 

you do however  have to start, you have to show up ,you have to get better consistently and you have to be committed to your dream and your goal no matter what life throws at you. 

 the best part is none of those things take any talent you can choose those choices right here right now

Drop a 🔥🔥 if this spoke to you

node.text:
➡️ are you frustrated right now?? 

good ! 

it means you are exactly where you’re supposed to be 

most people take frustration as a sign that something is wrong…it shouldn’t be this hard… i should be further by now

a leader sees frustration as confirmation they are on the right path 

most people let their frustration drive them to quit … a leader lets their frustration drive them to recommit 

winning consistently is a lot about how you manage frustration… …

does it take you off your game  or put you in the zone? 

here’s Three good reasons i’ve found most leaders are frustrated 

1. you care - most people are indifferent about their lives..the fact that you are frustrated means you care about the outcome

2. you’re growing - growth is frustrating because you are always playing at the edge of your competencies. that’s a good thing 

3. you’re skills need to improve - lacking the skillsets needed for the next level can be frustrating but it frustrates you forward into developing the toolset you will need in the next level 

DROP A 💯💯 if this spoke to you

node.text:
4 things that HURT now but PAY OFF later ….

1. Discipline- 
discipline is inescapable, we will either discipline ourselves or someone else will discipline us …

Choosing what you want most over what you want now is a  skill absent in virtually everybody. Will you accept short-term pain for long-term gain?

2. Self Improvement -
Nobody’s holding a gun to your head forcing you to get better… but things don’t get better until we get better.

Our very best thinking belief systems and habits have gotten us exactly what we have now if we ever want to have more, do more, and accomplish more, we first must become more…  internal victories will always proceed external ones

3.  Investing - 
Investing at the core whether it’s money, or time, or self-improvement is about holding back some of what you have now to invest into your future self

But here’s the truth: if you don’t invest in you why should anybody else. YOU have been and will always be your best investment.. You need to invest in your future because one day you’re gonna have to live there.

4. Self Control 
it’s easy today to be offended, to be angry, to give somebody a piece of your mind…. DON’T…. it’s a trap 

great leaders never lose their self control they always play it close to the vest…. 

When we don’t have self control we are out of control and end up being controlled by others or circumstances

keep your power, become  unoffendable, stay in control

node.text:
LONG POST ALERT 

Distraction= Destruction

most people are not incapable of achieving their dreams, they are just unfocused

most of the time our lives are not held back by bad things , but by good things in place of the best things 
 
the TRUTH is this: we could be doing big things if we weren’t so busy doing small ones 

 Our ability to focus for long periods of time on the most important things will determine the level of success we achieve

so here’s my top 3 steps to staying focused: 

1. Don’t over commit: when you say yes to something you say no to something else… make sure that you have space in your life to say yes to the things that move the needle 

2. Do the most important things early and consistently, that way if you only get a little bit done every day you’ve gotten the most important things done

3. Get clear about what you want- because when you don’t know where you’re going any path will get you there. we can avoid the rabbit trails of life by having a clear and compelling vision of our destination.

the best part is this :  FOCUS IS FREE
 it requires no talent and no cost to focus

so stop saying yes to everything so you have the time and energy to focus on the best things

node.text:
4 things that it takes to win:

1.  Total committment - 

there is but one level of committment : TOTAL. The price of success must be paid upfront and in full. 

2. Unparalleled work ethic -

hard work beats talent when talent doesn’t work hard. Work ethic is a choice , we’ve got to be the hardest worker in the room 

3.  Relentless self improvement - 

 what it takes to win is not something outside of us, but rather  something Inside of us.  If we are ever to have more, we must first become more. We can’t stay the same and expect our world to change 

4.  Mental Toughness -

You simply don’t win with your head, you win with your heart. so much of winning is holding on a little longer than everyone else. internal victories will always precede external ones 

What I love about winning is that ANYONE can win; not everyone will win, but everyone CAN win: why? 
because winning is not a talent winning is a CHOICE !!
